<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - LIGHT SYSTEMS - PANEL LIGHTS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x08260221">
        <title>PANEL LIGHTS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS</title>
            <figure id="f0826031" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0826071.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Panel Lights Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ELECTRICAL SYSTEM CONTROLLER (ESC)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. DRIVETRAIN 1939 DATA LINK BETWEEN ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER (EGC) AND ESC</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. EGC</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. DIMMER CIRCUITS CONTROLLED BY PANEL LIGHT SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. DIMMER SWITCH MOUNTED IN 3 SWITCH PACK MOUNTED IN EGC</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. DOOR PODS</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. SWITCH DATA LINK</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0826031">Panel Lights Function Diagram</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <para>Panel lights are low wattage bulbs that illuminate gauges and other miscellaneous items. The panel
                light switch provides input to the EGC which generates the voltage to dim/brighten the panel lights for
                the gauge clusters, speedometer/tachometer module, cigar lighter, door pods, heater control, etc.
            </para>
            <para>Most panel lights receive a control voltage directly from the EGC. The door pods receive dimmer
                control messages from the ESC on the switch data link.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
